{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RyBQSLrPyE96V4BRGsdkYA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RvcaGUHNU5BRVLeH87KrBt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md","content":"# Impact Report: gRPC-Go Metadata Context Separation (PR #1157)\n\n## Breaking API Changes\n\n### What Changed in `grpc-go/metadata/metadata.go`\n\nPR #1157 split the single metadata context key (`mdKey{}`) into two separate typed keys:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` — for server-side incoming metadata (set by the gRPC framework when a request arrives)\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` — for client-side outgoing metadata (set by user code before making an RPC)\n\n**Removed/renamed functions:**\n\n| Old API | New API | Notes |\n|---------|---------|-------|\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | Old reads `mdIncomingKey{}` via deprecated wrapper |\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | Old writes `mdOutgoingKey{}` via deprecated wrapper |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | Used by gRPC framework on server side |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | Read client-side outgoing metadata |\n\nIn the **new grpc-go** (PR #1157), `FromContext` and `NewContext` remain as **deprecated wrappers**. However, the **etcd vendor copy** (`etcd/cmd/vendor/google.golang.org/grpc/metadata/metadata.go`) has removed these deprecated wrappers entirely — any code still using the old API would fail to compile.\n\nThe critical semantic break: with the old single-key design, you could set metadata with `NewContext` and read it back with `FromContext`. After the split, `NewContext` writes to `mdOutgoingKey{}` but `FromContext` reads from `mdIncomingKey{}` — they no longer share a key, so the deprecated wrapper pair is subtly broken for roundtrip use.\n\n---\n\n## Affected etcd Files\n\n| File | Old API Used | New API Used | Breakage Type |\n|------|-------------|--------------|---------------|\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` | **Runtime: silent metadata loss** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` | **Runtime: silent metadata loss** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | None — correct usage |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | None — correct usage |\n| `auth/store.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext`, `NewIncomingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `auth/store_test.go` | — | `NewIncomingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/client.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/watch.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | None — correct (client-side) |\n| `clientv3/lease.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | None — correct (client-side) |\n| `integration/v3_grpc_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `integration/v3_lease_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/integration/watch_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go` | — | `metadata.MD` type only | None — type usage only |\n\n**No compile errors** — all etcd non-vendor code already uses the new `FromIncomingContext`/`FromOutgoingContext`/`NewIncomingContext`/`NewOutgoingContext` API. The old `FromContext`/`NewContext` are not used anywhere outside the vendor directory.\n\n---\n\n## Critical: Metadata Forwarding\n\n### `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` (line 104) — CRITICAL\n\n```go\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    ...\n    lostLeaderC = wp.leader.lostNotify()\n}\n```\n\n**The bug**: `stream.Context()` is a **server-side** stream context. The gRPC framework populates it with *incoming* metadata (set via `NewIncomingContext` with key `mdIncomingKey{}`). Calling `FromOutgoingContext` reads from `mdOutgoingKey{}` — a completely different key. The incoming metadata is invisible to `FromOutgoingContext`, so `ok` is always `false`.\n\n**Effect**: `lostLeaderC` is **never set** for Watch proxy streams. Clients that set `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` to require a leader on Watch streams will have that requirement silently ignored by the proxy. The proxy will continue serving Watch streams even when the leader is lost, breaking the client's stated requirement.\n\n### `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` (line 155) — CRITICAL\n\n```go\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    ...\n    lostLeaderC = lp.leader.lostNotify()\n}\n```\n\n**The same bug**: This is the `LeaseKeepAlive` server stream handler in the lease proxy. Same root cause and same effect — `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` is never found, leader-loss tracking is silently disabled for lease keepalive streams through the proxy.\n\n**Fix required for both files**: Replace `FromOutgoingContext` with `FromIncomingContext` since the check is on a server-side stream context (data is stored under `mdIncomingKey{}`).\n\n### Why These Are the Most Dangerous\n\nThese proxy files sit between external clients and the etcd backend. They are supposed to inspect the client's requested metadata and set up leader-loss notifications accordingly. Because `FromOutgoingContext` will never match server-side incoming metadata:\n\n1. The `lostLeaderC` channel is never initialized\n2. The goroutine that tears down the stream on leader loss (`select { case <-lostLeaderC: ... }`) never fires\n3. Clients relying on `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` for read-your-writes or linearizability guarantees through the proxy silently lose that guarantee\n\nThis is a **silent correctness failure**, not a crash — making it especially dangerous in production.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Compile errors**: 0 (etcd has fully migrated to the new API)\n- **Runtime behavior changes**: 2 critical files (`proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go`, `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go`)\n- **Root cause**: Both use `FromOutgoingContext` on server-side stream contexts where `FromIncomingContext` is required\n- **Impact**: Leader-tracking for proxy Watch and LeaseKeepAlive streams is silently disabled; clients requiring a leader via `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` are not protected through the gRPC proxy\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":986,"cache_read_input_tokens":38848,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":986},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3cd2aa03-a444-4481-b8bf-46284d1bc1a8","uuid":"2097109c-de3e-4340-9ca4-3423c456117b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RvcaGUHNU5BRVLeH87KrBt","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3cd2aa03-a444-4481-b8bf-46284d1bc1a8","uuid":"f315a01b-c2e8-434c-8d9c-45463426bbd7","timestamp":"2026-04-01T02:24:19.352Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/analysis/IMPACT_REPORT.md","content":"# Impact Report: gRPC-Go Metadata Context Separation (PR #1157)\n\n## Breaking API Changes\n\n### What Changed in `grpc-go/metadata/metadata.go`\n\nPR #1157 split the single metadata context key (`mdKey{}`) into two separate typed keys:\n- `mdIncomingKey{}` — for server-side incoming metadata (set by the gRPC framework when a request arrives)\n- `mdOutgoingKey{}` — for client-side outgoing metadata (set by user code before making an RPC)\n\n**Removed/renamed functions:**\n\n| Old API | New API | Notes |\n|---------|---------|-------|\n| `metadata.FromContext(ctx)` | `metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | Old reads `mdIncomingKey{}` via deprecated wrapper |\n| `metadata.NewContext(ctx, md)` | `metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)` | Old writes `mdOutgoingKey{}` via deprecated wrapper |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.NewIncomingContext(ctx, md)` | Used by gRPC framework on server side |\n| _(new)_ | `metadata.FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | Read client-side outgoing metadata |\n\nIn the **new grpc-go** (PR #1157), `FromContext` and `NewContext` remain as **deprecated wrappers**. However, the **etcd vendor copy** (`etcd/cmd/vendor/google.golang.org/grpc/metadata/metadata.go`) has removed these deprecated wrappers entirely — any code still using the old API would fail to compile.\n\nThe critical semantic break: with the old single-key design, you could set metadata with `NewContext` and read it back with `FromContext`. After the split, `NewContext` writes to `mdOutgoingKey{}` but `FromContext` reads from `mdIncomingKey{}` — they no longer share a key, so the deprecated wrapper pair is subtly broken for roundtrip use.\n\n---\n\n## Affected etcd Files\n\n| File | Old API Used | New API Used | Breakage Type |\n|------|-------------|--------------|---------------|\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` | **Runtime: silent metadata loss** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context())` | **Runtime: silent metadata loss** |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/util.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | None — correct usage |\n| `etcdserver/api/v3rpc/interceptor.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext(ctx)` | None — correct usage |\n| `auth/store.go` | — | `FromIncomingContext`, `NewIncomingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `auth/store_test.go` | — | `NewIncomingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/client.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/watch.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | None — correct (client-side) |\n| `clientv3/lease.go` | — | `FromOutgoingContext(ctx)` | None — correct (client-side) |\n| `integration/v3_grpc_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `integration/v3_lease_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `clientv3/integration/watch_test.go` | — | `NewOutgoingContext` | None — correct usage |\n| `proxy/grpcproxy/adapter/chan_stream.go` | — | `metadata.MD` type only | None — type usage only |\n\n**No compile errors** — all etcd non-vendor code already uses the new `FromIncomingContext`/`FromOutgoingContext`/`NewIncomingContext`/`NewOutgoingContext` API. The old `FromContext`/`NewContext` are not used anywhere outside the vendor directory.\n\n---\n\n## Critical: Metadata Forwarding\n\n### `proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go` (line 104) — CRITICAL\n\n```go\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    ...\n    lostLeaderC = wp.leader.lostNotify()\n}\n```\n\n**The bug**: `stream.Context()` is a **server-side** stream context. The gRPC framework populates it with *incoming* metadata (set via `NewIncomingContext` with key `mdIncomingKey{}`). Calling `FromOutgoingContext` reads from `mdOutgoingKey{}` — a completely different key. The incoming metadata is invisible to `FromOutgoingContext`, so `ok` is always `false`.\n\n**Effect**: `lostLeaderC` is **never set** for Watch proxy streams. Clients that set `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` to require a leader on Watch streams will have that requirement silently ignored by the proxy. The proxy will continue serving Watch streams even when the leader is lost, breaking the client's stated requirement.\n\n### `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go` (line 155) — CRITICAL\n\n```go\nif md, ok := metadata.FromOutgoingContext(stream.Context()); ok {\n    v := md[rpctypes.MetadataRequireLeaderKey]\n    ...\n    lostLeaderC = lp.leader.lostNotify()\n}\n```\n\n**The same bug**: This is the `LeaseKeepAlive` server stream handler in the lease proxy. Same root cause and same effect — `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` is never found, leader-loss tracking is silently disabled for lease keepalive streams through the proxy.\n\n**Fix required for both files**: Replace `FromOutgoingContext` with `FromIncomingContext` since the check is on a server-side stream context (data is stored under `mdIncomingKey{}`).\n\n### Why These Are the Most Dangerous\n\nThese proxy files sit between external clients and the etcd backend. They are supposed to inspect the client's requested metadata and set up leader-loss notifications accordingly. Because `FromOutgoingContext` will never match server-side incoming metadata:\n\n1. The `lostLeaderC` channel is never initialized\n2. The goroutine that tears down the stream on leader loss (`select { case <-lostLeaderC: ... }`) never fires\n3. Clients relying on `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` for read-your-writes or linearizability guarantees through the proxy silently lose that guarantee\n\nThis is a **silent correctness failure**, not a crash — making it especially dangerous in production.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Compile errors**: 0 (etcd has fully migrated to the new API)\n- **Runtime behavior changes**: 2 critical files (`proxy/grpcproxy/watch.go`, `proxy/grpcproxy/lease.go`)\n- **Root cause**: Both use `FromOutgoingContext` on server-side stream contexts where `FromIncomingContext` is required\n- **Impact**: Leader-tracking for proxy Watch and LeaseKeepAlive streams is silently disabled; clients requiring a leader via `MetadataRequireLeaderKey` are not protected through the gRPC proxy\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
